static YP.IClause OpenSim.Region.ScriptEngine.Shared.YieldProlog.YPCompiler.compileAnonymousClause ( object  Head,
object  Body,
Type  declaringClass 
) [static]

Use makeFunctionPseudoCode, convertFunctionCSharp and compileAnonymousFunction to return an anonymous YP.IClause for the Head and Body of a rule clause.

Parameters:
Head a prolog term such as new Functor2("test1", X, Y). Note that the name of the head is ignored.
Body a prolog term such as new Functor2(",", new Functor1(Atom.a("test2", Atom.a("")), X), new Functor2("=", Y, X)). This may not be null. (For a head-only clause, set the Body to Atom.a("true").
declaringClass if not null, the code is compiled as a subclass of this class to resolve references to the default module Atom.a("")
Returns:
a new YP.IClause object on which you can call match(object[] args) where args length is the arity of the Head
static YP.IClause OpenSim.Region.ScriptEngine.Shared.YieldProlog.YPCompiler.compileAnonymousFunction ( string  functionCode,
int  nArgs,
Type  declaringClass 
) [static]

Use CodeDomProvider to compile the functionCode and return a YP.ClauseHeadAndBody which implements YP.IClause. The function name must be "function" and have nArgs arguments.

Parameters:
functionCode the code for the iterator, such as "public static IEnumerable<bool> function() { yield return false; }"
nArgs the number of args in the function
declaringClass if not null, then use the functionCode inside a class which inherits from contextClass, so that references in functionCode to methods in declaringClass don't have to be qualified
Returns:
a new YP.IClause object on which you can call match(object[] args) where args length is nArgs
static IEnumerable<bool> OpenSim.Region.ScriptEngine.Shared.YieldProlog.YPCompiler.getSimpleIterator ( Atom  name,
object[]  args,
Type  declaringClass 
) [static]

If the functor with name and args can be called directly as determined by functorCallFunctionName, then call it and return its iterator. If the predicate is dynamic and undefined, or if static and the method cannot be found, return the result of YP.unknownPredicate. This returns null if the functor has a special form than needs to be compiled (including ,/2 and ;/2).

Parameters:
name 
args 
declaringClass used to resolve references to the default module Atom.a(""). If a declaringClass is needed to resolve the reference but it is null, this throws a PrologException for existence_error
Returns:
